│ happened; thus the failure is directly due to this fold.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe transformation assumes Cond and Cmp have identical types. However,     │
│ LLVM IR permits a scalar condition for vector selects (select i1, <N x T>, <N x T>). In that situation, Cond is i1, while Cmp (icmp on vector operands) is <N x │
│ i1>. The fold does not account for this mixed scalar/vector case and blindly builds (and/or Cmp, Cond), violating the IR type rules for binary operators (both  │
│ operands must share the same type). The same issue exists for the secondary inverted-condition fold (lines 3654–3658). The absence of a type compatibility      │
│ guard causes the assertion failure. Proper fix: only apply the fold when Cond->getType() == Cmp->getType(). Optional enhancement (not required for correctness) │
│ would be to broadcast the scalar Cond to a vector, but that would add instructions and is outside the intent of a peephole fold.\n\n4. Proposed Edit            │
│ Points:\nEdit Point 1 (lines 3628–3635): Wrap the creation of BinaryOperator in a type check. If types differ, skip the fold (return nullptr path continues).   │
│ Add a comment explaining why the fold is gated (reference PR/reproducer pr119063) to prevent future regressions.\nSuggested replacement logic within the        │
│ existing if-block:\n  Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, Other, Constant::getNullValue(Other->getType()));\n  // Only fold if the select condition type      │
│ matches the compare result type.\n  // Scalar select condition controlling vector operands (e.g. select i1, <vec>, <vec>)\n  // yields mismatched types (i1 vs  │
│ <N x i1>) and we cannot form a valid and/or.\n  if (Cmp->getType() == Cond->getType())\n    return BinaryOperator::Create(Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ ?           │
│ Instruction::And : Instruction::Or, Cmp, Cond);\n  // Otherwise, abandon this fold.\n\nEdit Point 2 (lines 3654–3658): Apply identical guard for the            │
│ inverted-condition case (using NotCond instead of Cond). After creating Cmp and NotCond, ensure Cmp->getType() == NotCond->getType() before creating            │
